Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.21,0:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.32,0:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a boisterous young man. {chapter 22}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.02,0:01:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, you're just fighting yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.59,0:01:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta think about other players at least a bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.86,0:01:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good manners!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.17,0:01:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I kan?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.37,0:01:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.54,0:01:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Itsuu Chankan Dora Dora, mangan.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.88,0:02:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, are you still not convinced?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.92,0:02:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}am{\i0} the rumored Calling Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.67,0:02:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, bud, you've been pretty quiet with your calls so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.70,0:02:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't do that, you announce them with a bang. {he's just commenting on Ryuu's bad manners in not properly announcing calls like he does, almost screaming}\N
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.70,0:02:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.68,0:02:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, watch this, bud.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.21,0:02:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna show you the essence of calling now. {no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.25,0:02:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, another 1-sou, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.99,0:02:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite appearances, you have guts, don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.32,0:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to call it.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.20,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the 4th 1-sou, won't you call it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.00,0:02:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Try me! {no clue: you said?}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.22,0:03:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Baiman?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.52,0:03:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it, self-proclaimed Calling Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.46,0:03:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The naked wait you're so proud of went down the drain. {waiting for one tile to finish one's pair and one's hand while the rest of one's hand is exposed; waiting for half of one's pair with four melds exposed​}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.41,0:03:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The famed Calling Dragon is defeated by a newcomer? {no clue what's ritte}{yaburetaritte toko kai / 破れたりって所かい}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.97,0:03:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk. Even the Calling Dragon loses sometimes.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.50,0:03:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you'd better not get carried away. \NWe know you're fake.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.53,0:03:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really think a sloppy thug like you
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.48,0:03:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,could make a convincing Calling Dragon from the rumors? {guess}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.65,0:03:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.15,0:03:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That one always keep his head down and remains stoic.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.12,0:03:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time he calls, \Na flash of light is produced,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.12,0:03:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because he imbues the tiles with life.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.32,0:04:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I'm not the real Calling Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.26,0:04:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The real one is long gone from this realm.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.18,0:04:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dragon is dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.28,0:04:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what's the point shooting the breeze with you? {guess}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.49,0:04:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, shall we start it?{muzu}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.60,0:05:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.77,0:05:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamicha{the player to your left} bud, is this why you called the 6-pin?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.11,0:05:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't called, your shimocha{player to the right} would've won by tsumo.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.23,0:05:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What ferocity, is it a Sanshoku Doukou? {sanshoku dou-pon again}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.66,0:06:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.93,0:06:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected of the Calling Dragon. \NHe's just the guy Ishikawa thinks he is.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.70,0:06:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost time, Boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.79,0:06:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sotoda, if that weasel doesn't bow down to me...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.85,0:07:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then kill him!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.32,0:07:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Boss?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.82,0:07:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's turn this into a festival... A festival of gunfire between east and west!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.80,0:07:27.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kaito Takeshi - now, he is considered the most powerful man in not just
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.41,0:07:30.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Kansai region, but within the entire Japanese underworld. {the onscreen text duplicates what's being said}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.71,0:07:32.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He leads the Kansai Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.66,0:07:35.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It includes well over 500 different organizations.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.49,0:07:43.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, he is the don that controls all of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.83,0:07:50.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to become the successor of the Oudou Syndicate,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.83,0:07:55.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa needed the Kaito seal of approval no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.64,0:08:06.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There was no one in Japan's underground world who didn't not know Kaito's name.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.08,0:08:10.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa is now sitting in front of that man.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.15,0:08:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, it must have been quite the hassle making the journey here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.82,0:08:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. The sight of Kyoto in the snow alone has made it most worthwhile.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.43,0:08:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics again.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.39,0:08:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yakuza don't need politics. \NIsn't that right, Ishikawa?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.67,0:08:31.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's swallowing me...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.30,0:08:37.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,To think that I, Ishikawa Takashi, would be so overwhelmed in the face of the don...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.49,0:08:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Boss?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.89,0:08:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.45,0:08:54.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That laugh was a sorrowful cry to Dragon, \Na cry that he would never hear.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.67,0:09:08.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dragon... Dragon! Do you dare to laugh at my face? My, Ishikawa Takashi's?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.86,0:09:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Kaito, I am Ishikawa Takashi, second leader of the Kai Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.90,0:09:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to Kyoto with the intention of giving my life up.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.88,0:09:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.72,0:09:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You came to Kyoto to give your life away, you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.86,0:10:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there really something of such importance here? Tell me more.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.73,0:10:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss Kaito, please do not continue to make a mockery of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.11,0:10:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know... Tomorrow this white snow may become a red rain!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.69,0:10:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss Kaitou, I shall state my request once more.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.19,0:10:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give me your approval when I become the new Oudou president!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.30,0:10:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This white snow may become a red rain tomorrow, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.37,0:10:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know, Ishikawa. \NThe weather migrates from west to east. {meaning that the winds in japan constantly blow from west to east, kyoto is located west of tokyo}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.17,0:10:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't that same crimson rain \Nfall in Tokyo the day after tomorrow?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.72,0:11:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's my advice, Ishikawa. \NHurry up back to Tokyo!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.29,0:11:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that some greenhorn from Sotoda-san's men dropped dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.00,0:11:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know - apparently, the red rain prefers the east over the west.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.88,0:11:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, I need to go out for a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.18,0:11:38.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Who could attack the Kai Group now...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.13,0:11:43.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,When I think about it, there's only one man who would rebel against me, the new boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.93,0:11:49.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At that moment, the name of Motomiya Haruki came to Ishikawa's mind clearly.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.87,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging from the car's license plate, it was Motomiya's work.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.78,0:11:57.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,So I thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.67,0:12:00.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,He's the only candidate I could think of.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.25,0:12:04.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only man idiotic enough to stand up to me, Ishikawa Takashi.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.11,0:12:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.38,0:12:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That was fun.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.67,0:12:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, when you see Ishikawa, tell him this:
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.54,0:12:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"You'll never usurp the syndicate for yourself."
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.61,0:12:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.81,0:12:34.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,Emergency exit {非常口}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.82,0:12:40.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Motomiya Haruki, the Brawler of Tokai.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.26,0:12:45.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He is one of those men \Nwho are born to become a yakuza.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.83,0:12:51.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He got tattooed when he was fourteen.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.27,0:12:56.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He lived his whole life without parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.71,0:13:00.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's why he chose two parents as the image to be put on his back. {chapter 24, no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.24,0:13:07.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Let me reiterate. He tattooed his back on his fourteenth summer.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.42,0:13:15.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He is Motomiya Haruki.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.95,0:13:18.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A yakuza by birth.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.44,0:13:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.19,0:13:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to say it again! C'mon!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.38,0:13:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Lieutenant was murdered!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.25,0:13:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A drowned body was found in Yokohama Bay at dawn today.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.69,0:13:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,After a short investigation, the man was identified as Wakabayashi Tamotsu,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.68,0:13:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,an executive staff at the Motomiya group, part of the Oudou syndicate.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.66,0:13:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Authorities believe it was a result of infighting between syndicates.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.42,0:14:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.37,0:14:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, you punk...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.88,0:14:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{page 45 of volume 4 for muzu}Oh, you had a good 2-man and 3-man double mentsu{a mentsu is a group of tiles, usually incomplete shapes} going on.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.71,0:14:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well done.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.38,0:14:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kid, you're trying to make fun of me, dontcha?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.45,0:14:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What an insistent 1-man.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.87,0:14:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.31,0:14:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A set-up with the 2-man and 3-man. {二萬三萬からの仕掛けじゃったのかい}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.85,0:14:49.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He said it was his habit to glimpse the shimmering landscape.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.05,0:14:52.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Motomiya was born in Yokohama
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.05,0:14:55.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Other than that, you won't get a word about his past out of him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.59,0:15:01.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We just know he like seagulls ever since he was a child.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.00,0:15:05.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He liked seagulls because they could fly freely anywhere they want.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.15,0:15:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, they got another one.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.66,0:15:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with those looks, you motherfuckers?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.60,0:15:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if they got a few of our guys?! \NHow can you even call yourself yakuza?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.91,0:15:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, this is a watershed moment!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.71,0:15:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going! \NFire from all guns! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.82,0:16:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta admit, Motomiya Haruki is going strong. Don't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.08,0:16:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so, the one defending is Ishikawa Takashi himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.83,0:16:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he stupid?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.93,0:16:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling again, kid?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.77,0:16:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh! I'm scared. \NSince this is the first call of the game.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.88,0:16:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{muzu}Hey, any more and my tenosynovitis... {なあ，これ以上わしの腱鞘炎をうずけさすなって}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.13,0:16:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.65,0:16:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...act up.  {think that's what he's on about}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.92,0:16:36.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Currently, Ishikawa
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.88,0:16:40.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,could see the shadow of the west behind Haruki Motomiya's back. {west here means kyoto}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.40,0:16:45.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Motomiya is indeed unrivaled when it comes to fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.19,0:16:50.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, even he wasn't stupid enough to start a fight he can't win.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.81,0:16:53.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The shadow of the west lingered distinctly behind Motomiya.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.61,0:16:57.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a giant shadow of Kaito Takeshi.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.35,0:17:10.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Motomiya was once again contemplating the shimmering landscape.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:21.04,0:17:25.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Of course, Motomiya knew that he was no match for Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.28,0:17:30.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Not because of a difference in organizational abilities,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.39,0:17:31.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but because of a certain "star"
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.95,0:17:35.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,everyone is born under, which Motomiya didn't quite understand himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.95,0:17:37.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite that, Motomiya...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.44,0:17:41.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,still wanted to fly higher than anyone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.96,0:17:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.97,0:17:59.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,By then, the messenger of the west \Nhad already visited Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.24,0:18:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.34,0:18:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.14,0:18:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya disappeared?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.22,0:18:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our men are seriously worried. \NPlease come back to safety.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.02,0:18:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya disappeared, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.77,0:18:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That cretin... Is he seriously aiming for my head?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.65,0:18:43.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,That man would come to me, even if he'd need to be disguised for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.62,0:18:48.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,And then he won't hesitate to take my life the moment I slip up.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.09,0:18:51.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of man he is.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.19,0:18:57.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That conviction was shared by gangsters who grew up on the same battlefield.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.74,0:19:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya-san, when my boss says something, he means it. You can trust him.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.78,0:19:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When he took control of the Kanto region, Motomiya-san,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.19,0:19:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he intended to put you in charge of the eastern part of the country.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.66,0:19:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one condition for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.69,0:19:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa Takashi - he wants you to do away with that man.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.40,0:19:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you hate his guts too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.14,0:19:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So why don't you take that man's head
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.49,0:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as a souvenir, \Nto the delight of both you and my boss?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.64,0:19:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, let me spell it clearly for you. {back to manga, page 75}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.25,0:19:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I went all the way to Tokyo to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.75,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is a certain someone asked me very politely to go and check on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.82,0:19:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you're a man
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.80,0:20:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who made even Ishikawa Takashi himself change his plans,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.90,0:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.60,0:20:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is to determine Ishikawa Takashi's worth using your evaluation.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.21,0:20:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. It's a good call, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.50,0:20:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.46,0:20:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All your calls are so terrifying, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.23,0:20:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, my tiles are all shiny and sparkling. {huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.67,0:20:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it now, Dragon. \NYou make your calls for others' sake.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.97,0:20:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got only one thing to tell you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.41,0:20:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.17,0:20:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As sad as it sounds, people only live for themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.78,0:20:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just you who keeps inquiring into others' lives. {人は悲しいほどに己れのために生きるもの\N他人のことしか問えない．．．あンた - this seems to be a very famous quote from this manga, but I for the life of me don't understand what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.15,0:20:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Foolish act.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.11,0:20:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya, if you're gonna come, come quickly!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.82,0:21:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help clear up your fucking hazy mind! {lit: wake up your half-asleep eyes}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.16,0:21:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, preparations are finished.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.59,0:21:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.70,0:21:19.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The waves were rocking the boat calmly.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.01,0:21:22.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A single seagull wandered around.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.11,0:21:25.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It wandered, as though in search of a place for repose.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.21,0:21:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.14,0:21:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.27,0:22:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.75,0:22:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.25,0:22:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're gonna shoot, do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.29,0:22:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop babbling, Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:16.80,0:22:19.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,Motomiya... \NWhy didn't you shoot?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:21.04,0:22:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.27,0:22:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:25.27,0:22:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.34,0:22:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As sad as it sounds, I am a creature that only lives for myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:36.08,0:22:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya, why didn't you shoot?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:37.85,0:22:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you giving me the final blow yourself?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.06,0:22:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.53,0:22:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For how long do you plan to keep humiliating me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:51.35,0:22:55.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As sad as it sounds, \Nthe sky was dreary that day.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.10,0:22:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme a gun.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.82,0:23:11.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.17,0:23:14.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The sky cried. {same word as in title}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.66,0:23:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,From what I could gather, Ishikawa and Motomiya
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.70,0:23:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have always been close, \Nand ate from the same bowl.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.27,0:23:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are disciples of the first boss of the Kai Group, Kai Shozo, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.21,0:23:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Dragon, doesn't that name bring back memories?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:35.61,0:23:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Kai Shozo.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.25,0:23:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That name is not an item of the past.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.41,0:23:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He still lives...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.79,0:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,inside me.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.44,0:24:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa! Pull the trigger already!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:08.48,0:24:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mo...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:17.45,0:24:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya...\NBoss Kai is crying in his grave... {naiteru is written in kana so I have no idea if it's "crying" or something else}{he's obviously not calling tiles in his grave}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:24.39,0:24:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya… Open your eyes! \NYou need to come to your senses...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:55.29,0:24:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you follow me for a minute?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:12.27,0:25:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get in.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:14.46,0:25:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain keeps splashing water into the car. {no clue what he means: 雨のしづくが車に忍びよる}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:25.85,0:25:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:28.21,0:25:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:30.46,0:25:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't start talking yet... {話はそれからじゃ - sorekara is marked with a dot so it's supposed to refer to some specific event, like "this story started back then..." or "we'll talk after we do that"}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:32.76,0:25:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not until you've properly righted the wrongs as a chivalrous man would. {おめぇがきちっと俠としてのおとしまえをつけてからじゃ - he uses otoko as in "chivalrous person, chivalry, knight-errant", also unsure what he's talking about, maybe it's just general "made up for your offense to me"}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:38.27,0:25:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:40.57,0:25:44.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unavoidably, the rain soaked Ishikawa's shoulders,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:45.54,0:25:48.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,adding to the weight of 2,000 lives already burdening it.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:07.36,0:26:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better move start moving, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:10.27,0:26:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My boss hates being made to wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:16.50,0:26:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:18.97,0:26:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,K-Kaito is in Tokyo!?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.30,0:26:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Say, you're quite certain of it, are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:25.58,0:26:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,T-They shoved Dragon into the car?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:30.41,0:26:37.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For Kaito Takeshi, Kanto - especially Tokyo - was a long-cherished dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.06,0:26:39.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He made it through endless ordeals.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:39.29,0:26:42.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was the one job he could never accomplish.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:42.83,0:26:44.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Conquer!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.57,0:26:49.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Lord Kaito Takeshi set foot on this land, \Nwhere he would meet his end. {not in manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.43,0:26:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it about Kaito Takeshi?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:56.68,0:26:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, aren't you guys gangsters and all?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.08,0:27:03.17,Top,,0,0,0,,Kaito is here alone, yet you're scared out of your wits.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:03.17,0:27:06.12,Top,,0,0,0,,You burst into tears over his sakura signboard. {no idea what she means: ”桜”の看板が泣いてあきれるわ}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.32,0:27:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.42,0:27:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{page 135 of volume 4}That's the one.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.69,0:27:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Another kanchan, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:14.36,0:27:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be 2,600{ points}.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.47,0:27:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad for you, boys.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.87,0:27:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm feeling very lucky today.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:38.65,0:27:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:41.59,0:27:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am... {Sakurada is not really his sister, that's just how yakuza call each other}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:55.70,0:27:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:04.18,0:28:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, watch me closely!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:06.85,0:28:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to right the wrongs like no one else ever did. Or ever would. {lit: I will now show you how I settle the scores once-in-a-lifetime}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.82,0:28:22.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At that time, Dragon
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.33,0:28:24.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was in that hell for a long time already.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:29.47,0:28:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, a call from madam Sakurada.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:33.14,0:28:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakurada?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:35.41,0:28:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She is crying over the phone.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:48.92,0:28:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa here.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:53.19,0:28:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:54.83,0:28:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I will personally take responsibility for Motomiya's life and protect him.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:00.23,0:29:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Madam Sakurada, please don't cry any more.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:03.20,0:29:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Madam...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:05.74,0:29:09.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Motomiya Haruki, 33 years old at the time.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:09.31,0:29:15.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was a handsome man, who still had that childlike image lingering on his profile. {/face}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:29.96,0:29:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, would you please kan this. {mockingly ordering him, because he knew Ryuu would do that anyway}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:34.77,0:29:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, it can't be this one, can it?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:53.62,0:29:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They said you were the poster child for luck, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:59.29,0:30:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But in our world, \Nyou can't win through sheer luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:03.70,0:30:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not unless you furnish it with a good strategy.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:08.30,0:30:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take the sky. {天は取れん - is this a mahjong area already?}{not really; but mahjong is connected to nature, earth, and heaven, like with the dragon tiles, which represent the elements, or the winds, which represent nature}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:09.74,0:30:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about heaven or earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:15.64,0:30:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only "now."
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.24,0:30:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In a blink of an eye, you
Dialogue: 10,0:30:24.38,0:30:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are not in this for much longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:36.63,0:30:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You big dumbass!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:40.66,0:30:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Think you can send your small fry to deal with me and call it a day?!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:46.61,0:30:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Small fry." \N"In this for much longer."
Dialogue: 10,0:30:52.01,0:30:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You easterners sure love to speak in some incomprehensible phrases.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:04.51,0:31:06.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:06.69,0:31:07.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:08.20,0:31:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to ask for a favor. \NPlease save Motomiya!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:13.02,0:31:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He came to see me last night, \Nand now he went to his death.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:16.02,0:31:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He apologized to everyone before dying.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:19.03,0:31:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Ishikawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:20.84,0:31:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it have to be this way?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:22.71,0:31:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Motomiya were as close as brothers, weren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:26.75,0:31:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this what it means to lead a gangster life?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:29.35,0:31:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it really have to be that extreme?!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:31.57,0:31:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:41.30,0:31:43.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't afford to lose Motomiya.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:03.58,0:32:08.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At that time, Motomiya was long chucking to himself, standing behind Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:10.56,0:32:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,First: Chivalry is about respecting justice. {that other otoko again}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:17.02,0:32:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Second: A chivalrous men would not be swayed by emotion.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:23.10,0:32:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Third: A chivalrous man lives for his lord. {主 doesn't have the reading oya so idk what to make of it}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:27.81,0:32:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's not afraid of death!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:33.28,0:32:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So scatter the fuck off! I am Motomiya Haruki from the Oudou Syndicate! {no clue what's the first part}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:51.10,0:32:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Motomiya-san, {\i1}you{\i0} are the small fry here.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:56.97,0:32:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaito...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:07.41,0:33:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid, didn't I tell you to stop?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:10.48,0:33:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just shameless. The true Calling Dragon is sitting here, right before you.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:15.46,0:33:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, bud.{muzu}{have no idea how to adapt"toimen no onii-san" (lit. buddy in front of me/ Toimen, buddy)}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:17.79,0:33:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You said this funny hooey before. \N"The Calling Dragon is not with us anymore?"
Dialogue: 10,0:33:22.46,0:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about. \NI'm right here, in flesh!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:28.64,0:33:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:47.89,0:33:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:54.29,0:33:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, never mind that. I said something thoughtless on the spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:58.50,0:34:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead, all right?\NHe's not with us anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:06.30,0:34:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,K-Kaito...
Dialogue: 10,0:34:11.81,0:34:14.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dragon… Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:15.52,0:34:17.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,Give me your luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:18.55,0:34:21.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,Give it to Motomiya!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:24.09,0:34:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, allow me to pon that one as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:30.59,0:34:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Dragon, with you in the game, tiles always move in interesting ways. {muzu check}{it's ok}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.60,0:34:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this also the doing of your good luck?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:39.67,0:34:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, Dragon,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:41.81,0:34:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but we'd like you to stick around for a wee bit longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:44.70,0:34:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, do you know why boss is sitting at a table with the likes of you?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:51.85,0:34:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the bait.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:54.69,0:34:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The delicious bait \Nthat attracts small fry.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:09.67,0:35:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that where your luck ends, Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:12.61,0:35:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know not the extent of my own luck. \NMuch less... {unsure: 己れを計る運など知らぬ}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:17.14,0:35:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If I have any luck to spare for others. {他人に授ける運など持たぬ}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:20.18,0:35:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say any more,
Dialogue: 10,0:35:23.15,0:35:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your words will lose any meaning. {白ける - no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:34.09,0:35:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:39.67,0:35:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:41.63,0:35:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon!!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:49.14,0:35:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaito...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:55.18,0:35:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Calling Dragon was killed alongside him back then.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:58.59,0:36:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaito's underlings did it. {no clue what's this deshitanyo}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:00.55,0:36:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:01.19,0:36:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:01.84,0:36:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:01.84,0:36:02.82,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:09.86,0:36:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill that man! Hurry up! Kill him immediately!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:17.17,0:36:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{again with toimen no onii-san}Hey bud.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:18.97,0:36:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this rubbish you're saying? {no clue whats hozoite}
